<paragraph blockId="6.[114,772,1789,2037]" lastBlockId="6.[817,1475,1469,1557]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
DISTRIBUTION. Mona Island. This species was erroneously described from 
<collectingCountry box="[296,433,1885,1909]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
: Cordillera Central: Cerro de Puntas, but 
<bibRefCitation author="ARMAS" box="[242,393,1917,1942]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="300" refId="ref3772" refString="ARMAS, L. F. DE. 2006. Presencia de Cazierius garridoi Armas, 2005 (Scorpiones: Scorpionidae) en Isla Mona, Puerto Rico. Boletin de la Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa, 38: 300." type="journal article" year="2006">Armas (2006)</bibRefCitation>
emended this mistake. It was also described by Santiago-Blay (2009) as 
<taxonomicName box="[551,718,1950,1973]" class="Arachnida" family="Diplocentridae" genus="Cazierius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tatae">
<emphasis box="[551,718,1950,1973]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Cazierius tatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but synonymized by 
<bibRefCitation author="ARMAS" box="[295,448,1981,2006]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="300" refId="ref3772" refString="ARMAS, L. F. DE. 2006. Presencia de Cazierius garridoi Armas, 2005 (Scorpiones: Scorpionidae) en Isla Mona, Puerto Rico. Boletin de la Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa, 38: 300." type="journal article" year="2006">Armas (2006)</bibRefCitation>
. In their study on the scorpion fauna of Mona Island, Teruel et al. (2017) provided additional data on its natural history an also suggested that this species might be a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Armas &amp; Marcano Fondeur, 1987)" baseAuthorityName="Armas &amp; Marcano Fondeur" baseAuthorityYear="1987" class="Arachnida" family="Diplocentridae" genus="Cazierius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cicero">
<emphasis box="[1171,1351,1502,1525]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Cazierius cicero</emphasis>
(Armas &amp; Marcano Fondeur, 1987)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1147,1305,1533,1557]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">the Dominican</collectingCountry>
Republic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
